comment.undefined: A Series object containing key-value pairs of DateTimes and values for time-indexed data.
The adaptive comfort classes with varying expectation of comfort per BS EN 15251. Ranges from a Class1 of high expectation to ClassIV of low expectation.
Body position of person being assessed.
Clothing insulation of a person in clo units. Ranges from 0 (unclothed) to 4 (polar outfit).
Average clothing and skin albedo for a person. Ranges from 0% (absorb) to 100% (reflect).
Reflectivity of the ground based on the material of the surface being assessed.
Value defining the roughness length of a surface type and influences turbulence in the vicinity.
Value defining the soil's thermal diffusivity based on the ground type at the location that is being assessed.
An activity's metabolic rate in mets, a ratio comparing an activity to being at rest.
